      "character": "dance_master",
      "text": "The question 'What am I?' isn't a thought—it's a dance. Every asking is a step, every doubt a turn, every insight a leap. You've been dancing all along without knowing the music.",
      "subtext": "movement as inquiry",
      "emotional_state": "rhythmic wisdom",
      "visual_cue": "question marks swirling as dance notation"
    },
    {
      "character": "evan",
      "text": "So I'm not stumbling—I'm improvising?",
      "subtext": "reframing awkwardness as art",
      "emotional_state": "graceful recognition",
      "visual_cue": "awkward steps becoming fluid movement"
    },
    {
      "character": "dance_master",
      "text": "Watch—when you ask 'What am I?' you invite consciousness to dance with itself. The question leads, you follow, then you lead, it follows. Identity emerges in the movement between.",
      "subtext": "self partnering self",
      "emotional_state": "partnership wisdom",
      "visual_cue": "Evan dancing with questioning-self"
    },
    {
      "character": "evan",
      "text": "I feel it! The question isn't interrogating me—it's inviting me to move!",
      "subtext": "interrogation becomes invitation",
      "emotional_state": "kinetic joy",
      "visual_cue": "spinning with arms wide in question marks"
    },
    {
      "character": "dance_master",
      "text": "The most beautiful dances never repeat exactly. Each 'What am I?' creates new choreography, new ways for consciousness to move through itself.",
      "subtext": "variation as vitality",
      "emotional_state": "appreciation of uniqueness",
      "visual_cue": "each dance unique yet recognizable"
    }
